    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis: non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA QoIs",
    "description": "Variance-based global sensitivity analysis (Sobol method, N=20000 model evaluations via PCE surrogate) was performed over eight input parameters: Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (E), yield strength (σ_y), tangent modulus (E_t), screw outer diameter (OD), thread pitch (p), friction coefficient at screw-block interface (μ), applied displacement rate, and UHMWPE block modulus. For construct stiffness, E and OD are dominant (first-order Sobol indices S_E=0.48, S_OD=0.31); for yield force, σ_y dominates (S_σy=0.57); for force at 40 mm, E_t and μ jointly dominate (S_Et=0.39, S_μ=0.22). Total-order indices confirm negligible higher-order interactions (all T_i − S_i < 0.05). These results guided the UQ sampling strategy and confirm that lot-specific material coupon data is the most critical input for model credibility.",
    "method": "Sobol variance decomposition via polynomial chaos expansion surrogate (order 3, sparse grid)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus",
      "screw outer diameter",
      "yield strength",
      "tangent modulus",
      "friction coefficient"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 20000
